n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n### .eslintrc.cjs\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n### vitest.config.ts\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n### .gitignore\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\n---\n\n## TASK.md (Main Project Description)\n\nThe project is to **build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch** that grows incrementally through 12 phases. Think of it like a simplified version of Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery -- entirely in-memory with no external dependencies.\n\nKey requirements:\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- All implementation in `src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies (dev dependencies already installed)\n- Must compile with `npm run build`\n- Must pass linting with `npm run lint`\n- Write tests as you go\n\nThe 12 phases are:\n1. Basic queue\n2. Named queues\n3. Priority\n4. Delayed tasks\n5. Retry with backoff\n6. Dead letter queue\n7. Task dependencies\n8. Concurrency control\n9. Progress and cancellation\n10. Recurring tasks\n11. Middleware\n12. Graceful shutdown\n\n---\n\n## Phase Requirements (All 12 Phases)\n\n### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Add tasks with payload, get back task object\n- Each task: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieving transitions task to \"processing\" state\n- Returns oldest pending task (FIFO)\n- Returns `null` if no tasks available\n- Way to check pending task count\n\n### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Tasks added to named queue (default queue if none specified)\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Retrieve from specific queue only\n- Creating queue happens implicitly on first task\n- Way to list all queue names\n- Non-existent/empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1 = highest, default = 5)\n- Higher priority (lower number) returned first\n- Same priority: FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities cause error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task exposes its priority level\n\n### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Tasks can have delay (ms) or specific future availability time\n- Delayed tasks not returned until available\n- Non-delayed preferred over delayed\n- Multiple delayed tasks: order by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task indicates when it becomes available\n- Works with named queues\n\n### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark processing tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks with retries re-added with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (1s, 2s, 4s, ...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Default base delay: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Exhausted retries: task in failed state\n\n### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Failed tasks (no retries left) moved to DLQ\n- DLQ associated with original queue\n- Way to view all dead-lettered tasks\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue for fresh retries\n- Way to clear all dead-lettered tasks\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can declare dependencies on other task IDs\n- Blocked tasks won't be returned when retrieving\n- Completing dependency unblocks dependent tasks\n- Circular dependencies detected and rejected at creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (remain blocked)\n- Way to inspect dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue max concurrency setting\n- Limits tasks in processing state simultaneously\n- Returns `null` if limit reached even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Way to set/query concurrency limit and active count\n- Respects priority ordering\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task can report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Way to query task's current progress\n- Listeners can subscribe to progress updates\n- Subscriptions cancellable (unsubscribe)\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n- Way to create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism evaluates schedules and enqueues tasks\n- Recurring tasks subject to all other rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Middleware registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips processing\n- Middleware can modify task (metadata, payload)\n- Middleware error marks task as failed\n- Handler registered per queue, invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown stops accepting new tasks\n- Adding tasks after shutdown produces error\n- Waits for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancels tasks exceeding timeout\n- Shutdown callbacks registered\n- Summary: completed count, force-cancelled count, duration\n- Multiple shutdowns safe and return same result\n- No processing tasks = immediate completion\n\n---\n\n## Source Directory\n\nCurrently, `/workspace/src/` is empty except for a `.gitkeep` file. This is where you'll implement the task queue system starting from `src/index.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a greenfield TypeScript project for building a sophisticated in-memory task queue system. The project:\n- Uses TypeScript 5.4+ with strict mode enabled\n- Has testing setup with Vitest\n- Has linting with ESLint and TypeScript support\n- Requires implementation of 12 increasingly complex phases\n- Is currently empty (ready for implementation)\n- Has no external runtime dependencies - pure JavaScript/TypeScript\n\nAll phase requirement files are detailed and ready for implementation in order from Phase 1 through Phase 12."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adef98d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 21018\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 35793</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f937c7ec-4fe1-4e16-8e08-5bf95aa13ded","uuid":"f88f5088-fd2c-4a13-bfbd-def83cefd831","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase structure. Show me:\n1. All files and directories\n2. Contents of package.json\n3. Contents of tsconfig.json\n4. Contents of TASK.md\n5. Contents of all files in the phases/ directory (all .md files)\n6. Contents of any existing src/ files\n7. Any config files (eslint, prettier, etc.)\n\nBe 