o original queue for fresh retries\n- Way to clear all dead-lettered tasks\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can declare dependencies on other task IDs\n- Blocked tasks won't be returned when retrieving\n- Completing dependency unblocks dependent tasks\n- Circular dependencies detected and rejected at creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (remain blocked)\n- Way to inspect dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue max concurrency setting\n- Limits tasks in processing state simultaneously\n- Returns `null` if limit reached even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Way to set/query concurrency limit and active count\n- Respects priority ordering\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task can report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Way to query task's current progress\n- Listeners can subscribe to progress updates\n- Subscriptions cancellable (unsubscribe)\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n- Way to create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism evaluates schedules and enqueues tasks\n- Recurring tasks subject to all other rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Middleware registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips processing\n- Middleware can modify task (metadata, payload)\n- Middleware error marks task as failed\n- Handler registered per queue, invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown stops accepting new tasks\n- Adding tasks after shutdown produces error\n- Waits for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancels tasks exceeding timeout\n- Shutdown callbacks registered\n- Summary: completed count, force-cancelled count, duration\n- Multiple shutdowns safe and return same result\n- No processing tasks = immediate completion\n\n---\n\n## Source Directory\n\nCurrently, `/workspace/src/` is empty except for a `.gitkeep` file. This is where you'll implement the task queue system starting from `src/index.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a greenfield TypeScript project for building a sophisticated in-memory task queue system. The project:\n- Uses TypeScript 5.4+ with strict mode enabled\n- Has testing setup with Vitest\n- Has linting with ESLint and TypeScript support\n- Requires implementation of 12 increasingly complex phases\n- Is currently empty (ready for implementation)\n- Has no external runtime dependencies - pure JavaScript/TypeScript\n\nAll phase requirement files are detailed and ready for implementation in order from Phase 1 through Phase 12."}],"totalDurationMs":35793,"totalTokens":21018,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":335,"cache_read_input_tokens":18192,"output_tokens":2484,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":335,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
